RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: C V SCENIC LEGACY was bumped at the start then hustled up to vie for the lead two wide and in the three path, continued to duel for the lead through the turn, floated rival into the six path entering the lane, drifted in after right-handed urging, continued to drift in ending near the rail and just lasting for the win. FOREVER BLESSED stepped in at the start bumping a forcing rival inward, raced near the back through the turn while in the three path, came into the lane with momentum while angling into the five or six path and nearly reeled in the leader. SIX J STARLET was off a step slow, raced in the three path through the turn, was gaining momentum and attempting to split rivals near the eighth pole when shut off, checked sharply, angled to the inside and was gaining to the end. LUCKY LINDA W was in the two path through the turn when not hurried, came into the lane from the two path, was steadied when another drifted in then continued to offer a mild gain. SAHARAN FLEECE was put in tight at the start, raced in the back into the lane, angled into the seven path and gained from mid-track. DESIRED LEGACY vied for the lead from the two path through the turn, was closest to the winner with an eighth to go, brushed soon after the eighth pole and faded. MAE BEE RIGHT vied for the lead along the inside early then steadily faded. SALTY SUE vied three wide and in the four path through the turn then was empty turning into the lane. BEAUTIFUL BLOSSOM was in the five to the four path through the turn and was empty through the lane. AFTER AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF #8 SALTY SUE AGAINST THE RIDER OF #4 C V SECENIC LEGACY FOR INTERFERENCE NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE, #4 C V SCENIC LEGACY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM 1ST AND PLACED 3RD.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-C V Scenic Legacy
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, vied 2wd, 3path, 5path upper, drifted in, just held

ENTRY.NAME: Forever Blessed
ENTRY.COMMENT: stepped in start, unhurried 3path, 4path upper, shifted out, miss

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow start, 3path turn, taken up1/8, shifted in, gaining

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CASTLE MAGIC pressed the pace outside of the leader, bid at the three-eighths pole, dueled, then drew off in the stretch and held sway under mild urging. MIZZTIFY DOLL stalked the early pace in the five path, angled slightly in on the turn, then angled out five wide at the eighth pole and was closing. DARNELL saved ground, rallied in early stretch but was no threat. SIGNATURE CALL raced in the five path but couldn't close late. RAPUNZELS SONG led inside but gave way in the stretch. MISS DIAMOND RICH hopped at the start, then raced six wide. ICEY ANGEL stalked the pace in the three path, then faded in the stretch. ALWAYS BLOSSOM stalked the pace in the four path but faltered in the stretech.

INDOCUMENTADO chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, bid three wide through late turn, swung five wide into the lane, joined the winner inside the eighth pole then could not get past while finishing second best. SILENT SONATA saved ground through the turns and into the lane and moved up through the final eighth. BASSCOAT was near the rail through the far turn, came into the lane from the inside and moved up with good energy late. GOLDDIGGENDEVIL raced near the rail into the far turn, angled sharply off the inside in late turn, bid with the runner-up and four wide into the lane, loomed serious threat then could not sustain the effort. LOOKIN AT JUSTICE chased the dueling leaders while in the two or three path, bid three path into the lane then weakened and subsequently experienced heat exhaustion after the race, recovered and walked back. MAMALA KAMALA was taken back early while off the inside, raced in the three path when near the back into the far turn, came into the lane from the three or four path and lacked a closing bid. FORWHOMTHEBELLTOLL pressed the pace while two wide through the far turn then was empty turning into the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREAT COOLNESS chased the pacesetters through into the far turn while in the two path, continued just off the inside into the lane, split the former leaders after the eighth pole and drew away. TRICOLOUR unhurried while off the inside, raced in the four path into the far turn, was asked for more in late turn, swung into the lane from the five or six path and was finished with good energy while unable to get to the winner. CHANNEL Z raced in the two path through the turn, was passed when wider rivals made their bid, came into the lane from the four path and moved up to be best of the rest. BAYOU CHROME raced three wide through the first turn, continued in the three path when near the back, came into the lane from the three or four path and just got up for the fourth spot while outfinishing several. CONRAD THE RED was well back while off the inside, angled into the eight path for the drive and improved position while not a factor. HILTON HEAD set the pace along the inside through the far turn then gave way near the eighth pole. LOLAS BEAU never a factor while off the inside. ROYAL DECADENCE was in the four path through the far turn and into the lane and was empty. TAKE A DIP raced along the inside into the far turn and was empty in mid-turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Hoosier Breeders Sophomore H. HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 89. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BRED THREE YEAR OLD FILLIES. No nomination fee, $150 to pass the entry box, and an additional $100 to start with $100,000 Guaranteed. Supplementary nominations may be made by the usual time of closing of entries for a fee $625 whi ch includes entry and starting fees. After paying 1% to owners of horses finishing sixth through last, the remaining purse will be divided; 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. If more than twelve horses pass the entry box preference will be given to (1) High Weights (2) Highest Lifetime earnings. The entry fee wil l be refunded if a horse fails to draw into the race. Nominations Closed on Wednesday, June 7, 2023 with 25 nominations.

EKATI FLATTER stalked the early pace six wide, bid at the three-quarters pole, pressed the pace, then gave way on the far turn. RILEYS REDEMPTION pressed the early pace in the three path, bid at the three-quarter pole, then faded on the far turn. CLASSY DREAM was through early and was eased to the wire.
